---
import Brand from '../layouts/Brand.astro';
---
<Brand title="Builders · usejarvis" description="Self-host Jarvis, source-available. Write YAML templates that teach the agent new apps, contribute them to the marketplace, and earn from every install." active="builders">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-in">
      <p class="label-mono reveal reveal-up">For builders</p>
      <h1 class="display-h1 reveal reveal-up">Self-host. Build templates. <em>Get paid.</em></h1>
      <p class="lead reveal reveal-up">Path 1 is for the technical power user. Run Jarvis on your own machine — source-available — write templates that teach it new apps, and contribute them to the marketplace. You become the supply side of the platform.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:11px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:26px" class="reveal reveal-up">
        <a class="btn-solid" href="/docs/installation">Install locally</a>
        <a class="btn-border" href="/docs/contributing">Contribution guide</a>
        <a class="btn-border" href="https://github.com/vierisid/jarvis" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section"><div class="section-inner">
    <div class="feat-grid reveal reveal-up">
      <div class="feat"><span class="fk">01 · Run</span><span class="ft">Self-host the daemon</span><span class="fp">Source-available. Your machine, your models — run local or bring your own keys.</span></div>
      <div class="feat"><span class="fk">02 · Teach</span><span class="ft">Write a YAML template</span><span class="fp">Describe an app's tasks in roles and ARIA. Test it live against the real app, watching Jarvis drive it.</span></div>
      <div class="feat"><span class="fk">03 · Earn</span><span class="ft">Ship to the marketplace</span><span class="fp">Contribute your template. When hosted users buy it, <b>you earn on a 70/30 split.</b></span></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section section-alt"><div class="section-inner">
    <p class="label-mono reveal reveal-up">What you're building</p>
    <h2 class="display-h2 reveal reveal-up" style="margin:12px 0 16px">Inventory that doesn't rot.</h2>
    <ul class="prose-list reveal reveal-up">
      <li><b>Roles and ARIA, not pixels.</b> Templates target the accessibility tree, so they survive UI refreshes instead of breaking on them.</li>
      <li><b>Any app a human can use.</b> Internal tools, niche SaaS, legacy systems — anything with a screen, no API required.</li>
      <li><b>Visible by construction.</b> Templates run on-screen where the user can watch, interrupt, and take over — the native path.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="cta-band reveal reveal-up" style="margin-top:30px">
      <div class="ctitle">Start building today.</div>
      <div class="csub">Install Jarvis, read the contribution guide, and ship your first template. The marketplace opens Q3–Q4 2026 — early builders supply it first.</div>
      <div class="cact"><a class="btn-solid" href="/docs/installation">Install locally</a><a class="btn-border" href="https://discord.gg/2HgF5krXrj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Builder community</a></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>
</Brand>
